==== ENTRY 1 ====
HEADWORD: Deplume
<hw>De*plume"</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>v. t.</pos> <vmorph>[<pos>imp. &
p. p.</pos> <conjf>Deplumed</conjf> <pr>(?)</pr>; <pos>p. pr. & vb.
n.</pos> <conjf>Depluming</conjf>.]</vmorph> <ety>[LL.
<ets>deplumare</ets>; L. <ets>de-</ets> + <ets>plumare</ets> to cover
with feathers, <ets>pluma</ets> feather: cf. <ets>deplumis</ets>
featherless, and F. <ets>d⟦eacute⟧plumer</ets>.]</ety> <sn>1.</sn>
<def>To strip or pluck off the feather of; to deprive of of
plumage.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>On the <qex>depluming</qex> of the pope every bird had his own
feather.</q> <rj><qau>Fuller.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><sn>2.</sn> <def>To lay bare; to expose.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><q>The exposure and <qex>depluming</qex> of the leading humbugs of
the age.</q> <rj><qau>De Quincey.</qau></rj>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

<p><ent>Depolarization</ent>⟦br⟧
